@NODE INTMACKE "THE INTERVIEW WITH MACKE/D.I. !!!"
  @{B}׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳@{UB}
                     @{fg highlight}    iNTERViEW WiTH MACKE/D.I.@{fg text}
  @{B}׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳@{UB}


   x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
   x @{FG HIGHLIGHT}iNTERvIEW with Markus / Digital Illusions (alias : Chevron / TSL)@{FG TEXT} x
   x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
                   x  @{FG FILL}by : SLASH! / iFFTic & cItRon.@{FG TEXT} x
                   x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
                     x  For the last iFFTic Chart! x
                     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-׳-׳


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Tell me a little about yourself? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                      ·
 ............................................................................

     For starters, My name is Markus and I`m currently involved in
 the development of Pinball Illusions. I started out in the year 1990 AD,
 in a group called Drakpak. Since then I`ve been a member of a couple of
 groups you wouldn`t care about. I`m Now a member of The Silents, and that's
 how it`s been for the last 3 years. Remember guys, TSL aren`t dead. The
 group can`t die before the last of us do. You could in BIG say that D.I is
 silents and the other way around. So that!
     I`ve done the graphics for quite a number of productions under the
 handle Chevron, but that was a long time ago, a looong time ago, and I`m
 not that proud of the most of it actually.
     I`m going on my Twentieth year as a person, and I`m defenately
 male, `n Thats about how much I will tell you werdos `bout me private life!
     Ok, I can aswell admit that I live in Gצteborg, but I`m planning to
 move to Stockholm. Not to meet the bloody people livin` there , but to
 study. I`m currently studying Public Relations.


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Why Pinball 3 ain`t coming to ECS machines? @{BG BACKGROUND}                           ·
 ............................................................................

     Well, what's in it for us? 150 copies sold and god knows how many
 copies spread by assholes! I can`t imagine that the ones reading this mag,
 if they got an ECS "Amצba", will buy the game anyway. If I`m wrong I do
 apologise! This may be true for many of the different formats around but
 the ECS is also too damn boring! Ugly goes without saying. Still, the rights
 to do an ECS version of Pinball 3 is available from us, if any of you guys
 are interested! I know that there are people out there capable of doing it
 almost as good as the AGA version!


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} How much money have you guys made? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                    ·
 ............................................................................

     You would like to know that wouldn`t you?!


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} How much money do you expect coming out of Pinball 3? @{BG BACKGROUND}                 ·
 ............................................................................

     I`m afraid the answer to this question would sound pretty much as
     the last.


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Why are you leaving Amiga? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                            ·
 ............................................................................

     Because it`s dead and burried, that`s why! Almost no developers will
 care about a machine like the Amiga. Hardly profitable, And everything below
 the A4000 is outshone by the simpliest of the consoles. People developing
 games also wanna have their fun you know! I believe though that the Amiga
 will be a format where new talents will emerge for a long time still. You
 can develop a game on an Amiga almost without any costs, and that`s not the
 reality if you look at the cost of, for example, a Playstation or Saturn
 developing kit. They`ll charge you up the ass you know!
     But maybe, if a new generation of Amigas will see the light of day
 and it shows that the market isn`t dead after all, we`ll be delighted to
 come back, `cause we all know that the Amiga is the best fuckin` machine
 around if your planning to do anything, and I mean anything without dying
 of herpes or something!


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} What on earth happened to Malfunction? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                ·
 ............................................................................

     Actually, Malfunction was never more than a good idea and
 some halfshitty screenshots. No that's not perfectly true, but the project
 was put on ice due to some economical problems or something (he he!:) )
     But you never know, someday maybe a game with the same idea but
 different looks will appear out of nowhere and wipe the competition.
 (Well almost).


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} When is Hardcore due to be released? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                  ·
 ............................................................................

     If we knew that, we would be a happy bunch of guys, really.
 The game is still in development but it`s slowly coming together, with
 emphasize on slowly! (Come on Bossprruullff, you`re killing us!)
     If luck`s travelling with us maybe in the early 95.
 (or 2004, or something)


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} How did you get the idea of making a pinball s(t)imulator? @{BG BACKGROUND}            ·
 ............................................................................

     It was actually some unknown guy called Mikael Balle, who showed
 some tables he`d been sketching on some cold summermornings to Animal,
 alias Fredrik, back in 1988, I think it was. And the rest is as you say
 history. (God I hate that old textclichee!)


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Whats your personal highscore on the different Pinball tables? @{BG BACKGROUND}        ·
 ............................................................................

     Personally I don`t have any highscores. They are more like
 lowscores or something! I hate Pinball. I would rather learn to write my
 name backwards and mirrored with my left foot than playing Pinball for
 more than 10 min. in a row! So therefore I`ll give you a collection of D.I;s
 highscores. "TRUE!".

     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
     x@{BG FILL} Pinball Dreams @{BG BACKGROUND}           x
     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

     Ignition:                   73.655.000
     Steel wheel:               354.800.000
     Beat box:                1.700.567.000
     Nightmare:                 955.030.000

     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
     x@{BG FILL} Pinball Fantasies @{BG BACKGROUND}        x
     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

     Partyland:                 586.400.000
     Speed devils:              712.800.000
     Stones n Bones:            950.786.000
     Billion dollar gameshow: 2.467.390.000

     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x
     x@{BG FILL} Pinball Illusions @{BG BACKGROUND}        x
     x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

     Law n Justice:             734.900.000
     Babewatch:                 ???.???.???
     Extreme sports:            ???.???.???
     Vikings:                   ???.???.???


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Whats your opinion of the scene? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                      ·
 ............................................................................

     Well, What can I say. If you`ve been a part of it, And I refere to
 myself as a former Elitescene guy if thats OK?, you`ll have a big problem
 getting away from it. It always happens something interesting, and its
 quite a thing we got here isn`t it. I have always thought that the scene
 is full of cool guys, sometimes though, with a little funny look on life.
     I`ve never taken part in any discussions like who`s lame, why we
 don`t need swappers and why Neonazis should or should not and bla bla bla,
 and thats how its gonna stay. If I got a meaning or opinion I`ll certainly
 keep it to myself or my closest friends. Words are so easyily misunderstood,
 turned upside down and insideout. I mean, perhaps people will write shit
 about this interview (who knows??). I`ll never see it because I only take My
 stuff from a single board, and that board ain`t Swedish. (Which sysop cares
 about a guy who calls maybe 1 time a month, and that results only in Dload.
 Because thats me in a nutshell)
     I only know that the face of the scene is changing, and it have
 been for quite a while now. What the result will look like is yet to be
 seen, if it ever stop changing that is.
     Read William Gibsons great books to see the future.


 ············································································
 ·  @{BG FILL} Do you have anything to add? @{BG BACKGROUND}                                          ·
 ............................................................................

     Hmmmm, let`s see.

     -Amiga is dead, long live the Amiga-
     -Where did all you old guys go, see you at the Party 4?-
